CSS NOTES
See more here:
https://www.w3schools.com/css/default.asp
Inline: Writen in the same line as html tag. Fx: <p style="color:blue;text-align:center;"> Hello world! </p>

Internal: 
Written inside the <head> tag fx:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <style>
      body {
        background.color: linen;
      }
      h1 {
        color: maroon;
        margin-left 40px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1> This is a heading</h1>
    <p> This is a Paragraph</p>
  </body>
</html>

External:
An external .css file, linked in the head, with a relationship definition.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1> This is a heading</h1>
    <p> This is a Paragraph</p>
  </body>
</html>
